Clinton to Select Cory Booker for VP Within the Week

Presumptive Democratic nominee Hillary Clinton has selected Cory Booker as her runningmate, according to multiple campaign staffers

Clinton and Booker stop for lunch in Cedar rapids in January.
By
Kate O’Keeffe and
Byron Tau
  • Byron Tau
    The Wall Street Journal
    CANCEL
  • BiographyByron Tau
  • @ByronTau
  • byron.tau@wsj.com
Updated July 7, 2016 10:08 p.m. ET

BREAKING NEWS: Hillary Clinton is expected to pick Cory Booker, the junior Senator from New Jersey, as her running mate. Sources tell The Journal that Clinton will reveal this announcement within the week, as opposed to after the Republican Convention as previously planned. This change in strategy is most likely an attempt to divert attention away from Clinton’s email scandal, which has been receiving increased scrutiny after FBI Director James Comey’s recent announcement. Sources close to The Journal have provided this information but wish to remain anonymous.

This is a developing story.
